  "body": "According to [this issue](https://github.com/mds1/convex-shutdown-simulation/issues/7), Hardhat might be returning an incorrect gas usage. The reason why this is a possibility is that the value is different from the Tenderly one, which is very likely to be correct. Notice that Foundry also matches the value from Tenderly, albeit with a small difference because they subtract the base tx and calldata costs.",
